Key Match Events: Brandon Nimmo's three-run homer capped a nine-run fourth
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Mets finished 11-2 against the Nationals this season, their best record against one opponent since going 10-1 versus the Los Angeles Dodgers in 1988
Others: Jose Quintana extended his scoreless streak to a career-high 22 2/3 innings
The Mets moved a season-high 16 games above.500
